headline: 5 Revealing Analyst Questions From News Corp’s Q2 Earnings Call
summary: News Corp’s second quarter results landed slightly above Wall Street’s expectations for both revenue and non-GAAP profit, but sales were essentially flat compared to last year, and the market response was muted. Management attributed performance to continued margin discipline, cost control, and targeted growth in its core pillars: Dow Jones, Digital Real Estate Services, and Book Publishing. headline: NWSA Q2 Deep Dive: Flat Revenue, Segment Investments, and Strategic Portfolio Shifts
summary: Global media and publishing company News Corp (NASDAQ:NWSA) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $2.11 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.19 per share was 5.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
